etymologies: mid 19th century: from modern Latin Strongylus, from Greek strongulos ‘round’

definitions: a nematode of a group that includes several common disease-causing parasites of mammals and birds.

notes.text: Genus Strongylus or family Strongylidae, class Phasmida. See also red worm (sense 2)

shortDefinitions: nematode worm of group that includes several common disease-causing parasites of mammals and birds
